  "text": "As discussed in [CITATION_1] , this formula can be regarded as a series 5 of transformations from the body coordinate b (for local joint) of each joint to the spatial coordinate s (for global kinematic chain). Let us focus on a joint j and denoteξ (b) andξ (s) the twists of this joint in the body and spatial coordinates, respectively. Assume the transformation of this joint to the spatial coordinate is g Θ1:j−1 = eξ 1 eξ 2 · · · eξ j−1 . The two twists can be related by the adjoint representation",
